data.chText: 我知道他的观点对他们很有影响力。
data.enText: I knew his opinion carried a lot of clout with them.
a blow with the hand or a hard object
to hit sb hard, especially with your hand

example: I gave him a clout on his nose

tr: a short nail with a flat head
used to attach sheet metal to wood

example: the chairman's nephew has a lot of pull

tr: strike hard, especially with the fist

value.def: If you clout someone, you hit them.

example.ex: The officer clouted her on the head.
I was half tempted to give one of them a clout myself.
example.tran: 我自己都特别想给他们某个人一拳。

value.def: A person or institution that has clout has influence and power.

example.ex: Mr Sutherland may have the clout needed to push the two trading giants into a deal...
example.tran: 萨瑟兰先生也许有能力促使两大贸易巨头达成协议。

example.ex: The two firms wield enormous clout in financial markets.
example.tran: 两家公司在金融市场有非常大的影响力。
